= Anderson|first2 = D.|title = The Madagascar Fauna Group|pages = 1543\u20131545|year = 2003|ref = harv}}\n:*{{cite book|last1 = Britt|first1 = A.|last2 = Iambana|first2 = B.R.|last3 = Welch|first3 = C.R.|last4=Katz|first4=A.S.|title= Restocking of ''Varecia variegata variegata'' in the R\u00e9serve Naturelle Int\u00e9grale de Betampona|pages = 1545\u20131551|year = 2003|ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book|editor1-last = Goodman|editor1-first = S.M.|editor2-last = Patterson|editor2-first = B.D.|title= Natural Change and Human Impact in Madagascar|publisher = Smithsonian Institution Press|year = 1997|isbn = 978-1-56098-682-9}}\n:*{{cite book|last = Simons|first = E.L. |title= Natural Change and Human Impact in Madagascar|chapter=Chapter 6: Lemurs: Old and New|pages = 142\u2013166|year = 1997|ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book|editor1-last = Gould|editor1-first = L.|editor2-last = Sauther|editor2-first = M.L. |title=Lemurs: Ecology and Adaptation |url = https://books.google.com/?id=nsBtrhsMU5EC&printsec=frontcover&q|publisher = Springer|year = 2006|isbn = 978-0-387-34585-7}}\n:*{{cite book|last1 = Gould|first1 = L.|last2 = Sauther|first2 = M.L.|chapter = Preface|title = Lemurs: Ecology and Adaptation|pages = vii\u2013xiii|year = 2006|ref = harv}}\n:*{{cite book|last=Tattersall|first = I.|chapter=Chapter 1: Origin of the Malagasy Strepsirhine Primates|title=Lemurs: Ecology and Adaptation|pages=3\u201318|year = 2006|ref = harv}}\n:*{{cite book|last1 = Jolly|first1 = A.|last2 = Sussman|first2 = R.W.|chapter=Chapter 2: Notes on the History of Ecological Studies of Malagasy Lemurs |title=Lemurs: Ecology and Adaptation |pages = 19\u201340|year = 2006|ref = harv}}\n:*{{cite book|last1 = Godfrey|first1 = L.R.|last2 = Jungers|first2 = W.L.|last3 = Schwartz|first3 = G.T.|chapter=Chapter 3: Ecology and Extinction of Madagascar's Subfossil Lemurs |title=Lemurs: Ecology and Adaptation |pages = 41\u201364|year = 2006|ref = harv}}\n:*{{cite book|last1 = Cuozzo|first1 = F.P.|last2 = Yamashita|first2 = N.|chapter=Chapter 4: Impact of Ecology on the Teeth of Extant Lemurs: A Review of Dental Adaptations, Function, and Life History |title=Lemurs: Ecology and Adaptation |pages = 67\u201396|year = 2006|ref = harv}}\n:*{{cite book|last1 = Fietz|first1 = J.|last2 = Dausmann|first2 = K.H.|chapter=Chapter 5: Big Is Beautiful: Fat Storage and Hibernation as a Strategy to Cope with Marked Seasonality in the Fat-Tailed Dwarf Lemur (''Cheirogaleus medius'') |title=Lemurs: Ecology and Adaptation |pages = 97\u2013110|year = 2006|ref = harv}}\n:*{{cite book|last = Curtis|first = D.J.|chapter=Chapter 7: Cathemerality in Lemurs |title=Lemurs: Ecology and Adaptation |pages = 133\u2013158|year = 2006|ref = harv}}\n:*{{cite book|last1 = Sterling|first1 = E.J.|last2 = McCreless|first2 = E.E.|chapter=Chapter 8: Adaptations in the Aye-aye: A Review |title=Lemurs: Ecology and Adaptation |pages = 159\u2013184|year = 2006|ref = harv}}\n:*{{cite book|last = Johnson|first = S.E.|chapter=Chapter 9: Evolutionary Divergence in the Brown Lemur Species Complex |title=Lemurs: Ecology and Adaptation |pages = 187\u2013210|year = 2006|ref = harv}}\n:*{{cite book|last = Irwin|first = M.T.|chapter=Chapter 14: Ecologically Enigmatic Lemurs: The Sifakas of the Eastern Forests (''Propithecus candidus'', ''P. diadema'', ''P. edwardsi'', ''P. perrieri'', and ''P. tattersalli'') |title=Lemurs: Ecology and Adaptation |pages = 305\u2013326|year = 2006|ref = harv}}\n:*{{cite book|last1 = Powzyk|first1 = J.A.|last2 = Mowry|first2 = C.B.|chapter=Chapter 16: The Feeding Ecology and Related Adaptations of ''Indri indri'' |title=Lemurs: Ecology and Adaptation |pages = 353\u2013368|year = 2006|ref = harv}}\n:*{{cite book|last = Tan|first = C.L.|chapter=Chapter 17: Behavior and Ecology of Gentle Lemurs (Genus ''Hapalemur'') |title=Lemurs: Ecology and Adaptation |pages = 369\u2013382|year = 2006|ref = harv}}\n:*{{cite book|last = Wright|first = P.C.|chapter=Chapter 18: Considering Climate Change Effects in Lemur Ec